Perspectives of Language Research in the Age of Artificial Intelligence\par
In an era where technological achievements are reshaping reality, language\f1\emdash the foundation of human communication, culture, and identity\emdash is no longer solely the domain of philological research. This conference aims to bring together academia and industry in the field of language technologies. We invite submissions addressing empirical, theoretical, and methodological questions related to the themes below.\par
\par
Key Themes\par
NLP and Artificial Intelligence\par
Novel models for language understanding, including large language models\par
Semantic analysis, entity recognition, and text categorization\par
Adaptation of NLP models for less-represented languages\par
Automated language processing systems for sentiment and dialogue\par
Real-world NLP applications in chatbots and translations\par
Digital Language Reality and Data in Global Society\par
Digital literacy and impact of new media on language structures\par
Collection of language data in digital environments\par
Differences between digital and traditional spoken language\par
Language rights and policy in digitalization context\par
AI's influence on language communities and preservation\par
Machine Translation and Language Analysis Algorithms\par
New approaches to machine translation (neural networks, transformers)\par
Algorithm adaptation for specific language pairs\par
Techniques for improving accuracy of machine translation\par
Integration of machine translation with NLP methods\par
Automation of proofreading processes\par
Ethics and Social Impact of Language Technologies\par
Privacy and data protection in NLP and language processing\par
Biases in language models and algorithms\par
Impact on employment, especially in translation and journalism\par
Ethical approaches for developing models for smaller languages\par
Application in social contexts and implications for inclusion\par
